{
  "stem": "24346.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the people from the area, because to go to the synagogue-- every day was consuming, and Saturday you could never make it there on foot, it was distant-- so this was the answer, that the people from this area prayed in shtiebels.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One of our own men was considered the hazzan, you know, who prayed before us, and everybody followed.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we didn't have a known Rabbi, no.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we had-- the people from the congregation had their own rabbi, hazzan, and everything.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I went only one Saturdays.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember, since I became bar mitzvah, I had to put [NON-ENGLISH] every day, every day except Saturday, of course.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I prayed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I had to pray, but I did at home, because I had to go to school.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So my brothers and I, we prayed at home.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, there was quite a bit of anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How should I say it?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was this Polish party, [NON-ENGLISH], they call them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We called them, in Yiddish, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They used to come into Jewish quarters and start fights with sticks, canes.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They wore canes, and they started fights.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "However, in our area where we lived, Balut-- or Baluty they call it in Polish-- we formed a resistance, because there lived certain tougher people from the Jewish population, meaning they were butchers.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they were really able to-- they were strong people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were not scared.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In other words, if they lifted the cane, they could stop them by grabbing the cane and fight back.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so in our area, we didn't see it so much.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "However, in the other areas, what we called the [NON-ENGLISH], where they lived, it was more like that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, not really.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "However, I have seen them marching on May the 3rd, which was a national Polish holiday.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
